## Migration Safety

### Safe Operations

```ruby
# These are safe (no downtime):
- add_column (with default: nil)
- add_index (without unique constraint, or with CONCURRENTLY)
- add_foreign_key (with validate: false)
- remove_column (after code is deployed)
- rename_column (with alias in model)
```

### Unsafe Operations

```ruby
# These can cause downtime:
- remove_column (if code still uses it)
- rename_column (if code references old name)
- change_column_null (to null: false)
- add_column (with default: not nil and null: false)
- add_index (without CONCURRENTLY on large tables)

# Solution: Multi-step deployment
# 1. Deploy code changes first
# 2. Run migration after
```

### PostgreSQL-Specific Safety

```ruby
# Add index concurrently (no locks)
class AddIndexToArticles < ActiveRecord::Migration[8.0]
  disable_ddl_transaction!
  
  def change
    add_index :articles, :title, algorithm: :concurrently
  end
end

# Add foreign key without validation
def change
  add_foreign_key :articles, :users, validate: false
end

# Validate later
def change
  validate_foreign_key :articles, :users
end
```

